 face of white resistance that cast them as perpetual aliens. Amezcua charts the diverse strategies used by Mexican Chicagoans to fight the forces of segregation, economic predation, and gentrification, focusing on how unlikely combinations of social conservatism and the real estate market savvy paved new paths for Latinx assimilation. Making Mexican Chicago offers a powerful multiracial history of Chicago that sheds new light on the origins and endurance of urban inequality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aMexican American neighborhoodszIllinoiszChicagoxHistoryy20th century. 0aMexican AmericansxHousingzIllinoiszChicago. 0aMexican AmericanszIllinoiszChicagoxHistoryy20th century. 0aMexicanszIllinoiszChicagoxHistoryy20th century. 0aSegregationzIllinoiszChicagoxHistoryy20th century. 0aUrban renewalzIllinoiszChicagoxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aLatino politics, spatial segregation, racial capitalism, Mexican immigration, Mexican Americans, white flight, real estate, urbanism, gentrification, political economy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2022 Englishz978311099296008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2022z9783110992939oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073919008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107665090 cprintz978022681582440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226815831423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/97